  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to conduct a translational study in patients with primary
      eosinophil associated gastrointestinal disorders [EGID] (e.g. eosinophilic esophagitis
      eosinophilic gastritis, eosinophilic enteritis [EE], eosinophilic colitis, and eosinophilic
      gastroenteritis [EGE]) with the aim of developing a data bank containing pertinent patient
      demographic information, tissue samples, and DNA, which will facilitate research on the
      pathophysiology of inflammatory disorders and the development of a verified successful
      clinical treatment program.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
